Difference Between /k and /c
Command	Meaning
/k	Run command and keep terminal open
/c	Run command and close terminal
Example /k
cmd /k dir
Result:
✅ shows files
✅ terminal remains open


Example Without /k
start cmd nodemon server.js


Real Example

@echo off
start cmd /k nodemon api.js
start cmd /k nodemon auth.js
start msedge.exe http://localhost:3000

This:
✅ opens 2 terminals
✅ runs 2 servers
✅ opens browser automatically

CMD Flow
cmd
 ├── /k → keep open
 └── /c → close after execution


